quran[55]{c,v,t}:
  54,1,The Hour (the time when the present world will end and the Hereafter begin) has drawn near and the moon is visited
  54,2,"And if they see a sign they turn away and say, \"Another delusion"
  54,3,And they speak lies and follow their own desires. And every matter does come to a settlement
  54,4,And surely there has come to them some of the news containing lessons
  54,5,In mature wisdom; but warnings avail not
  54,6,So turn away from them on the Day when the Summoner summons to a thing forbidding
  54,7,"With downcast eyes, they come out of the graves as though they were locusts dispersed"
  54,8,"Hurrying on toward the Summoner, the suppressors of Truth say, \"This is a hard day"
  54,9,"Before them, Noah's people had denied! They denied Our devotee and said he was a mad man! And thus rebuffed was he"
  54,10,"Then he prayed to his Lord, \"I am defeated, so help me"
  54,11,We then opened gates of the sky with pouring water
  54,12,"And We caused springs in the earth to gush forth, so that the waters met for a predestined purpose"
  54,13,"And We carried him [Noah] upon something [Ark made] of planks and nails"
  54,14,"That sailed under Our observation, in compensation for one [Noah] who was rejected"
  54,15,"And We did leave it [Ark] behind as a Sign for posterity; but is there any to take heed"
  54,16,And see how My punishment was — and My warnings
  54,17,And We have certainly made the Qur'aan easy for cultivating Firm Faith in and Remembrance of Me; but is there any to take heed
  54,18,"(The anscient tribe of) AAad rejected [divine guidance]. How then was My punishment and My warnings"
  54,19,We did indeed send upon them a furiously blowing wind on a day of constant calamity
  54,20,"It [wind] swept away men as though they were trunks of uprooted palm-trees"
  54,21,How then was My punishment and My warnings
  54,22,And We have certainly made the Qur'aan easy for cultivating Firm Faith in and Remembrance of Me; but is there any to take heed
  54,23,(The ancient tribe of) Thamood rejected warnings
  54,24,"They said, \"Is it an individual man, amongst us all, that we should follow? Then we are indeed into error and madness"
  54,25,"Is the Zikr [divine revelation] bestowed only upon him, amongst us all? Nay, but he is an insolent liar"
  54,26,To-morrow they shall know who the insolent liar is
  54,27,We are indeed sending the she-camel by way of a test for them. Just watch them and have patience
  54,28,And tell them that the water is to be shared among them; every drink to be accounted for
  54,29,But then they prevailed upon one of their companions to take hold of and hamstrung (her)
  54,30,How then was My punishment and My warnings
  54,31,"We sent upon them just one loud, piercing sound, and they became as the dry twigs used by the builder of a cattle-fold"
  54,32,And We have certainly made the Qur'aan easy for cultivating Firm Faith in and Remembrance of Me; but is there any to take heed
  54,33,Lot's people rejected warnings
  54,34,"We did indeed send a violent storm upon them all save the family of Lot, whom We saved in the wee hours before dawn"
  54,35,As favour from Us. Thus do We reward a grateful one
  54,36,"And he did warn them of Our Grip, but they had doubts on the veracity of the warnings"
  54,37,"And they did try to seduce him about his guests. So We blinded their eyes, \"Taste now My punishment and My warnings"
  54,38,And the punishment decreed did befall them early in the morning
  54,39,Taste then My punishment and My warnings
  54,40,And We have certainly made the Qur'aan easy for cultivating Firm Faith in and Remembrance of Me; but is there any to take heed
  54,41,And warnings did come to the house of Pharao
  54,42,"They denied all Our Signs. Therefore We gripped them with a mighty, powerful Grip"
  54,43,"Are your Truth-suppressors better than those [mentioned above], or have you some immunity [decreed for them] in the Scriptures"
  54,44,Or do they claim they are a united front
  54,45,The front will soon be routed and put to flight
  54,46,"Moreover, the Hour (the time when the present world will end and the Hereafter begin) is their tryst with destiny, and the Hour shall be more grievous and bitter"
  54,47,The sinners are indeed into error and madness
  54,48,The Day they are dragged into the Fire upon their faces to taste the feel of Hell
  54,49,We have indeed created every thing to a measure
  54,50,And Our Command is just one! Like the twinkling of an eye
  54,51,And We did destroy the likes of you; but is there any to take heed
  54,52,And every thing they did is in the Records
  54,53,"And everything, small and big, is duly recorded"
  54,54,The pious indeed will be among gardens and rivers
  54,55,Seated in honour near the Most Powerful King